headline: S&P Global and Barclays Partner on a Multi-Year Strategic Agreement
summary: S&P Global (NYSE: SPGI) today announced the signing of a new multi-year strategic agreement with Barclays. The mutually beneficial agreement includes access to a comprehensive suite of S&P Global products, data, and solutions, powered by S&P Capital IQ Pro platform, to support Barclays' businesses across its enterprise and help enhance the bank's offerings to its own customers. headline: CARFAX: Fridays Pose Highest Risk for Car Accidents on U.S. Roads
summary: Fridays are the riskiest day for car accidents for most U.S. drivers, according to new data from CARFAX. More accidents occur on Fridays than on any other day of the week in at least 43 states, with the end of the work week rush likely a contributing factor. By contrast, Sundays were the quietest on U.S. roads, with the fewest incidents reported in almost all states."Drivers need to stay vigilant anytime they're on the road," said Chief John Fisher of the Bedford, Mass., Police Department.
